Business Brief -- International Multifoods Corp.:
   Agricultural Operations Sale
   Completed for $146 Million
The operations, which include Multifoods' U.S. and
Canadian animal feed and grain merchandising businesses, were
sold to AGP, a joint venture 80%-owned by Ag Processing Inc.,
a grain processing and merchandising company in Omaha, Neb.,
and 20%-owned by Archer-Daniels-Midland Co., an agricultural
commodities company based in Decatur, Ill.
   The sale included 18 animal feed plants, 26 retail
agricenters, and 18 grain elevators in the Midwestern and
Eastern U.S.; and 11 animal feed plants and a hatchery in
Canada. The businesses' annual net sales are $230 million.
They employ 970 people.